<br>
there must have been a misunderstanding of some sort regarding mobs and such.  <br>
<br>
most people dont schedule plane raids every two days though, out of simple respect for giving others a chance.  theoretically, i can be in guild x and schedule hate every two days for 2 weeks.<br>
<br>
although, there isnt a rule saying you cant do that, it generally isnt done.  and believe me, if somebody tried, the bitching would ring clearly through MT.<br>
<br>
if you absolutely must schedule a raid every 2 days, feel free. but as an aside, i think its only fair to point out if its done regularly, people will get upset.  a couple of raids in a row is no biggie, but any clear monopoly of the calendar by any one person and/or guild will be stopped just for the sake of fairness to the other dozen or so guilds that schedule.  <br>
<br>
afterall, the only reason we have a calendar and rules is to give everyone a chance.<br>
<br>
as far as the revised rules go, i like them.  it was an oversight on my part never to update the rules.  as soon as i get a moment, i will update those.   well done!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crystilla>crystilla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 404<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/16/02 1:29:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: calendar rules</span><hr size=1> Woot Jes spoke!  Thx for putting down an answer to this for us hun! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=janson01>Janson01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/16/02 4:17:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: calendar rules</span><hr size=1> Calendar is a gentleman agreement. not &quot;rules&quot;<br>
